if (Cases[I - 1]->getValue() != Cases[I]->getValue() + 1)
```

This checks if Cases[I-1] == Cases[I] + 1, i.e., if the previous value is one more than the current value. This would be true for descending order like {7, 6, 5}:
- I=1: Cases[0] = 7, Cases[1] = 6, 7 == 6 + 1? Yes
- I=2: Cases[1] = 6, Cases[2] = 5, 6 == 5 + 1? Yes

So `constantIntSortPredicate` sorts in DESCENDING order!


